"""
    Test of get_e_interp
    """
age_wgts = np.ones(80) * 1 / 80
test_vals = income.get_e_interp(80, age_wgts, age_wgts, abil_wgts, plot=True)
print('test vals = ', test_vals)
assert np.allclose(test_vals, expected_vals)
pytest.mark.parametrize('abil_wgts,expected_vals', [(abil_wgts1,
    expected_vals1), (abil_wgts2, expected_vals2)], ids=['default weights',
    'non-default weights'])
